Rule: Higher education levels (Masters, Prof-school) are associated with a positive income outcome.
Being married is associated with a positive income outcome, even with the same education level (HS-grad).
Working in non-private sectors (Other/Unknown, Self-Employed, Government) is associated with a positive income outcome.
Being male is associated with a positive income outcome, even with similar education and workclass.
Being in a Blue-Collar occupation within the Government sector is associated with a positive income outcome.
